    funFact: "The Guinness World Record for the most four-leaf clovers found in one hour stands at 166, set by an American clover hunter in 2018. Scientists have found that a single genetic mutation — a recessive trait — causes the fourth leaf, and some clover patches have higher rates of the mutation than others, creating genuine 'lucky spots.'",
